gate: LOCKED
sprint: S04
track: B
task: B2
title: "bug(api): MAX_PAGE_SIZE silent clamp → return 400 not Math.min (#1292)"
repos: [crop-front]
priority: P2
refs:
  - CROP-front#1292
requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND, TYPESCRIPT]

description: |
  request-utils.ts silently clamps page size to MAX_PAGE_SIZE via Math.min.
  Callers receive fewer results than requested with no indication that their
  input was out of range — this hides integration bugs. Fix: validate page size
  at the boundary and return 400 with a clear error message when it exceeds MAX.

scope:
  in:
    - lib/request-utils.ts (or equivalent) — replace Math.min clamp with validation + 400
    - Error message: "pageSize exceeds maximum of {MAX_PAGE_SIZE}"
    - Unit test: pageSize > MAX → 400; pageSize <= MAX → proceeds normally
  out:
    - Changing MAX_PAGE_SIZE value
    - Any other param validation beyond pageSize

acceptance:
  - Request with pageSize > MAX returns 400 with descriptive message
  - Request with pageSize <= MAX proceeds as before
  - Unit tests cover both paths

dep: none
output: request-utils.ts patched + unit tests
